20th century on the Web
The first television history site has been established on the Internet, and it is linked to the name of Hungarian producer, János Zolcer.
The most important Hungarian and international events of the last century can be reviewed on the TV website: 100 years - 100 stories - dramatically told in 100 films.
We will hear from witnesses of the age, such as the last survivor of the Titanic, Al Capone's nephew, Hitler's secretary, the first men on the moon, the first test-tube baby, and the unsuccessful assassin of the Pope. Leading politicians of the age will also be presented including Helmut Kohl, Shimon Peres, George Bush and Mikhail Gorbachev...
